sender.description:
This is the identifier of the sender, it is a json object of the form:
  {
    "emailAddress":"...",
    "name":""
  }
"name" is optional.

recipients.description:
This is a json array representing the recipients of the email. The array is of the following form:
[
  {
    "emailAddress":"...",
    "name":"..."
  }
]  

The "emailAddress" is the recipient's email. The "name" is optional and when present represents the
name of the recipient.

attachments.description:
This is a json array representing a list of file attachments. The array is of the following form:
[
  {
    "path":"../",
    "description":".."
  }
]

The "path" is the path of the file to attach. "name" represents the name of the file 
and "description" describes the files.

embeddedImages.description:
This is a json array representing a list of local images embedded in the message via "img" tag. 
The array is of the following form:
[
  {
    "path":"../"
  }
]
The "path" field must be the same as the path specified in "src" attribute of the corresponding "img" tag.
This array must only include local file embeds, ie not files embedded via a remote http url.

